    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-15T16:53:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-15T16:53:00-05:00" n="304"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d304">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/1–1552: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d304fn1">This telegram, which was drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_SCOTTWK1">Scott</persName> (<gloss target="#t_EUR1"
                            >EUR</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss>), cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_GODLEYGMII1">Godley</persName> (<gloss target="#t_EUR1"
                            >EUR</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss>), and signed by <persName
                            corresp="#p_PERKINSGW1">Perkins</persName> for the Secretary, was
                        repeated for information to The Hague.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-15T16:53:00-05:00"
                            >January 15, 1952—4:53 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4085. For <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_MACARTHURDII1">MacArthur</persName>. <persName
                        corresp="#p_BEGOUGNEDEJUNIACG1">De Juniac</persName>, Acting Minister
                    Counselor Fr <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>, called on <persName
                        corresp="#p_PERKINSGW1">Perkins</persName> this morning under instrs to ask
                    us <pb facs="0630" n="586" xml:id="pg_586"/> to make clear to <persName
                        corresp="#p_DREESW1">Drees</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d304fn2">Netherlands Prime Minister <persName
                            corresp="#p_DREESW1">Drees</persName> made an informal visit to the
                        United States between Jan. 12 and 24. Regarding that visit, see <persName
                            corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1">Acheson</persName>’s memorandum of his
                        conversation with <persName corresp="#p_DREESW1">Drees</persName> on Jan.
                        21, <ref target="#pg_589">p. 589</ref>.</note> US support of <gloss
                        target="#t_EDF1">EDF</gloss> and US desire that <gloss target="#t_Benelux1"
                        >Benelux</gloss> join. <persName corresp="#p_PERKINSGW1">Perkins</persName>
                    told <persName corresp="#p_BEGOUGNEDEJUNIACG1">de Juniac</persName> this wld be
                    done but that our info re current Dutch worries this subj was to effect Dutch
                    more worried about Fr attitudes than about US views. Pointed out specifically
                        <persName corresp="#p_STIKKERDU1">Stikker</persName>’s worry about <persName
                        corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName>’s remark re ephemeral character
                        <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>.<note n="3" xml:id="d304fn3">In
                        telegram 686, Jan. 9, from The Hague, Chargé <persName
                            corresp="#p_TRIMBLEWC1">Trimble</persName> reported on a conversation
                        with Foreign Minister <persName corresp="#p_STIKKERDU1">Stikker</persName>
                        during which <persName corresp="#p_STIKKERDU1">Stikker</persName> quoted a
                        statement by French Foreign Minister <persName corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1"
                            >Schuman</persName> made at the Six-Power Meetings of Foreign Ministers
                        in Paris, Dec. 27–30, to the effect that the <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                            >EDC</gloss> would be the lasting defense organization for Europe
                        whereas <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> was only transitory and
                        “essentially ephemeral”. (740.5/1–952)</note> Said our understanding was
                    that Dutch were genuinely wedded Atlantic community concept and did not wish to
                    participate in <gloss target="#t_EDF1">EDF</gloss> in such a way as to prejudice
                    that concept. Asked <persName corresp="#p_BEGOUGNEDEJUNIACG1">de
                        Juniac</persName> urge his <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> do what
                    it cld calm Dutch fears re <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>/<gloss
                        target="#t_EDF1">EDF</gloss> relationship.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BEGOUGNEDEJUNIACG1">De Juniac</persName> said Fr Amb Hague
                    reports large majority Neth Parliament solidly behind <gloss target="#t_EDF1"
                        >EDF</gloss> but that Neth Govt less enthusiastic. Within Cabinet identified
                        <persName corresp="#p_DREESW1">Drees</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_STIKKERDU1">Stikker</persName> and Lieftinck as being least
                    enthusiastic. We did not challenge this although we had assumed here that
                        <persName corresp="#p_DREESW1">Drees</persName> by far most reluctant member
                        <gloss target="#t_Cab1">Cab</gloss> re <gloss target="#t_EDF1"
                    >EDF</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Expect here to rpt to <persName corresp="#p_DREESW1">Drees</persName> points
                    included Secy’s conversation <persName corresp="#p_VANROIJEN1">Van
                        Roijen</persName> Jan 10 (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 904, Jan
                    11, rptd Paris 4018<note n="4" xml:id="d304fn4">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_580">p. 580</ref>.</note>).
                        <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>s Paris and Hague requested let us know
                    whether they wish these or any other points re <gloss target="#t_EDF1"
                        >EDF</gloss> especially emphasized with <persName corresp="#p_DREESW1"
                        >Drees</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
